snippet.title: Amber Heard - The aqua queen.
snippet.description:
Amber Heard biography,age,family,income and early life.

Hello friends, Welcome to our business one channel, How are doing today. Lets get started
Amber Laura Heard was born on April 22, 1986 is an American film and television actress.
 After a series of small roles in film and television, Amber Heard had her first starring role in the horror film All the Boys Love Mandy Lane (2006).
Amber Heard first gained mainstream recognition for supporting roles in the action film Never Back Down (2008) and the comedy Pineapple Express (2008).
In the following years, Amber Heard appeared in films such as The Joneses (2009), The Ward (2010), The Rum Diary (2011), Drive Angry (2011), Machete Kills (2013) and Magic Mike XXL (2015).
In 2017, Amber Heard joined the DC Extended Universe to play Atlantean queen Mera in superhero films Justice League (2017), Aquaman (2018), and Zack Snyder's Justice League (2021).
In addition to acting, Amber Heard has been a global spokesperson for the cosmetics giant L'Oréal Paris since 2018. Amber Heard also engages in human rights activism.
Amber Heard was married to actor Johnny Depp from 2015 to 2017. Their divorce drew significant media attention as Amber Heard alleged that he had been abusive through most of their relationship. 
Johnny Depp then sued her for defamation in 2019 after Amber Heard  wrote an op-ed discussing being a public victim of domestic violence. 
Johnny Depp also sued the publishers of The Sun in a related libel suit in England. 

In 2020, the High Court of Justice of England and Wales ruled that Johnny Depp had lost his libel case and that the majority of Heard's allegations had been proven to a civil standard.
Amber Heard was born in Austin, Texas, to Patricia Paige, an internet researcher (1956–2020), and David Clinton Heard (born 1950), who owned a small construction company.
Amber Heard earliest acting work included appearances in two music videos, Kenny Chesney's "There Goes My Life" and Eisley's "I Wasn't Prepared", and small supporting roles in the television series Jack & Bobby (2004), The Mountain (2004), and The O.C. (2005).

Amber Heard gained moderate mainstream recognition in 2008 with supporting roles in the Judd Apatow-produced stoner comedy Pineapple Express and the martial arts drama Never Back Down, both of which were box office successes. 
In 2017, Amber Heard appeared as part of an ensemble cast in Lake Bell's indie comedy I Do... Until I Don't and joined the DC Extended Universe (DCEU) cast as Mera, Aquaman's Atlantean queen, in the superhero film Justice League.
Amber Heard is an ambassador for the American Civil Liberties Union (ACLU), to whom Amber Heard pledged half of her divorce settlement, and a Human Rights Champion for the Stand Up for Human Rights campaign by the Office of the United Nations High Commissioner for Human Rights.
Amber Heard publicly came out in 2010, but has stated, "I don't label myself one way or another—I have had successful relationships with men and now a woman. 
Amber Heard and Johnny Depp began dating in 2012 and were married in a civil ceremony in February 2015. In April 2015, Heard breached Australia's biosecurity laws when she failed to declare her and Depp's two dogs to the customs when they flew into Queensland, where he was working on a film.
Amber Heard pleaded guilty to falsifying quarantine documents, stating that she had made a mistake due to sleep deprivation.
Hope you guys are enjoying my videos, Please do not forget to subscribe our channel  for upcoming videos, We appreciate your view and being our valued viewer, have a nice day and stay safe.
